<p>The <code>now</code> function returns the current Unix timestamp.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}now{close}</pre>
<p>Current timestamp: <b>{now}</b></p>

<h2>Format with Date</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y-m-d'){close}</pre>
<p>Today: <b>{now | date('Y-m-d')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('H:i:s'){close}</pre>
<p>Current time: <b>{now | date('H:i:s')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y'){close}</pre>
<p>Current year: <b>{now | date('Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('F j, Y'){close}</pre>
<p>Full date: <b>{now | date('F j, Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('l'){close}</pre>
<p>Day of week: <b>{now | date('l')}</b></p>

<h2>Calculations</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y') | + 1{close}</pre>
<p>Next year: <b>{now | date('Y') | + 1}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('m') | + 0{close}</pre>
<p>Current month number: <b>{now | date('m') | + 0}</b></p>
